Wiper leader Kalonzo Musyoka has reignited the National Super Alliance (NASA) presidential debate, saying he was the best suited to be the Opposition flag bearer. Kalonzo &nbsp;made his first trip to Kisii after their maiden NASA rally in Bomet on Saturday. Speaking at various shopping centres in Kisii County,&nbsp; Kalonzo said he had talked to other Nasa leaders to allow him become the alliance&rsquo;s flag bearer. &ldquo;NASA has the answers to your prayers,&rdquo; said Kalonzo. Kalonzo was speaking during a tour to drum up support for the party&rsquo;s Kisii gubernatorial aspirant Lumumba Nyaberi. The Wiper leader is expected to continue with his Kisii tour.